## Dead Ends
- Top-level export from weave.integrations (import-safety, above).
- Reusing weave.session Session/Turn agent_name as the override source: those CREATE
  their own invoke_agent span, so auto-instrumentation under them would get a
  redundant second invoke_agent span. Rejected.
- Patch-time agent_name argument: timing-fragile under implicit/singleton patching;
  forces one name per process. Rejected for the ContextVar.
- Sub-agent nested invoke_agent spans + naming: investigated, then dropped by the
  user ("ignore my tangent").

## Hints for Future Agents
- DO NOT export anything from weave/integrations/__init__.py that transitively
  imports an optional integration package at module top. It runs on `import weave`.
- The override is SCOPE-WIDE: resolve_agent_name reads the ContextVar, so EVERY
  invoke_agent span created inside an agent_name_override(...) block takes the name.
  For claude that is always exactly 1 span/turn (fine). For openai handoffs (multiple
  agent spans) they would ALL get the same name. If you ever need strict
  "1 CM = 1 span", implement consume-for-descendants (outermost agent consumes the
  override; nested fall back). Not done here on purpose.
- claude_agent_sdk OTel emits exactly 1 invoke_agent per query/turn. It IGNORES
  parent_tool_use_id, so sub-agent (sidechain) messages currently fold into the root
  invoke_agent as extra `chat` spans. There is NO nested invoke_agent / separate
  weave trace for sub-agents (the SDK's separate "session" for sidechains,
  isSidechain:true, is CLI-internal storage, not a weave span). If you add nested
  sub-agent spans, name them from the Task ToolUseBlock.input["subagent_type"]
  (auto, like openai's sd.name) — a context manager cannot reach an auto-spawned
  sub-agent.
- Resolve once at span creation (claude does this in _trace_turn on the first
  __anext__, which runs inside the user's `with` block, so the ContextVar is visible).
- openai _call_name is SHARED with the legacy (calls) path — do not route the
  override through it; only the AgentSpanData branches in otel_processor were changed.

## Codebase Discoveries
- invoke_agent_attributes (weave/session/session_otel.py) is the single emitter of
  gen_ai.agent.name across integrations — that is why the reviewer said "they all
  write to gen_ai.agent.name anyways."
- Precedence chosen: explicit override > integration-native name > integration default.
- openai-agents API churn: AgentSpanData/Span/Trace exist in 0.2.0, but the test
  module also needs TaskSpanData/TurnSpanData (newer). The lock pins 0.2.0; the nox
  shard must use a newer version in CI.

